184
00:11:48,705 --> 00:11:51,332
[woman] And as bodies are
being pulled out of the rubble,

185
00:11:51,416 --> 00:11:54,502
another factory in Bangladesh caught fire
early this morning,

186
00:11:54,586 --> 00:11:56,004
killing eight more people.

187
00:11:56,671 --> 00:12:00,633
[narrator] As story after story
of disasters kept filling the news,

188
00:12:00,717 --> 00:12:04,012
it was now the case that three
of the four worst tragedies...

189
00:12:04,095 --> 00:12:08,016
...in the history of fashion had
all happened in the last year.

190
00:12:08,099 --> 00:12:11,227
As the death toll rose,
so did the profits generated.

191
00:12:11,311 --> 00:12:13,980
The year following the disaster
at Rana Plaza was

192
00:12:14,063 --> 00:12:17,108
the industry's most profitable
of all time.

193
00:12:17,192 --> 00:12:19,235
The global fashion industry is now

194
00:12:19,319 --> 00:12:22,197
an almost $3 trillion annual industry.

195
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:24,490
[man]
Bangladesh is now the second largest

196
00:12:24,574 --> 00:12:26,910
apparel exporter, after China.

197
00:12:26,993 --> 00:12:29,621
How? Well, unlike some
of its competitors,

