didn't give a damn shit.

203
00:12:50,058 --> 00:12:53,061
They just wanted the cheap price
and a good profit.

204
00:12:53,144 --> 00:12:54,729
It shouldn't be like that.

205
00:12:54,812 --> 00:12:58,107
Everybody should take
the responsibility for those kids.

206
00:13:02,904 --> 00:13:04,489
That's how it is.

207
00:13:05,657 --> 00:13:07,283
There might be more coming.

208
00:13:07,367 --> 00:13:11,746
Sorry, but you know that it's not only
the price pressure,

209
00:13:11,829 --> 00:13:13,039
it is something--

210
00:13:13,122 --> 00:13:14,916
Ignoring other people's lives.

211
00:13:14,999 --> 00:13:18,336
It's not... It shouldn't...
It's not right.

212
00:13:18,419 --> 00:13:20,338
It's the 21st century.

213
00:13:20,421 --> 00:13:22,131
It's a global world we are living in,

214
00:13:22,215 --> 00:13:25,134
and we just ignore other people's lives?

215
00:13:25,218 --> 00:13:26,344
How come?

216
00:13:26,427 --> 00:13:30,390
This enormous, rapacious industry

217
00:13:30,473 --> 00:13:32,809
that is generating so much profit

218
00:13:32,892 --> 00:13:35,061
for a handful of people,

219
00:13:35,144 --> 00:13:37,605
why is it that it is unable

220
00:13:37,689 --> 00:13:41,317
to support millions
of its workers properly?

221
00:13:41,401 --> 00:13:45,613
Why is it that it is not able
to guarantee their safety?

222
00:13:45,697 --> 00:13:47,782
We're talking
about essential human rights.

223
00:13:47,866 --> 00:13:49,868
Why is it unable to guarantee that

224
00:13:49,951 --> 00:13:52,996
whilst generating
these tremendous profits?

225
00:13:53,079 --> 00:13:54,998
Is it because it doesn't work properly?

226
00:13:55,081 --> 00:13:56,374
That is my question.

227
00:13:58,042 --> 00:14:00,545
[narrator] Lucy's question sounds
like the obvious one.

228
00:14:00,628 --> 00:14:03,631
But instead of answering it,
everywhere I looked, I found people

229
00:14:03,715 --> 00:14:05,842
who were constantly justifying the cost

230
00:14:05,925 --> 00:14:08,511
because of the economic benefits
being generated.

231
00:14:08,595 --> 00:14:12,849
So, this low-wage manufacturing,
or so-called "sweatshops,"

232
00:14:12,932 --> 00:14:15,643
they're not just the least bad option
